    • Method Detail

      • location

        public UploadOptions.Builder location(java.lang.String location)
        Set the location where the file will be stored. For locations other than s3 the file will be first stored in Filestack's internal S3 bucket and then moved to a proper location. If empty or not valid the file will be stored in S3 bucket configured for the selected application (if configured) or in Filestack's internal S3 bucket.
        Parameters:
        location - s3, gcs, dropbox, azure, or rackspace

      • region

        public UploadOptions.Builder region(java.lang.String region)
        Set an S3 region for the selected S3 bucket. If container(String) is provided and this is empty, the application will try to get the region from database or directly from Amazon.

      • container

        public UploadOptions.Builder container(java.lang.String container)
        Set the name of the container where the file will be stored.

      • path

        public UploadOptions.Builder path(java.lang.String path)
        Set the path where the file will be stored. By default, the file is stored at the root of the container at a unique id, followed by an underscore, followed by the filename. Paths ending with / will be treated as folders where the files will be stored in a similar way. Ignored if the file is stored in Filestack's internal S3 bucket.

      • access

        public UploadOptions.Builder access(java.lang.String access)
        Set if the file should be stored in a way that allows public access going directly to the underlying file store. If empty or the file is stored in Filestack's internal S3 bucket it defaults to private.
        Parameters:
        access - private or public

      • intelligent

        public UploadOptions.Builder intelligent(boolean intelligent)
        Sets if the upload should use Filestack Intelligent Ingestion. This must also be enabled on your account to work, if not it will be ignored.

      • build

        public UploadOptions build()
        Create the UploadOptions instance using the configured values.
